text: Martina Šurnovská (born 10 February 1999) is a Slovak footballer who plays as a midfielder and has appeared for the Slovakia women's national team. ==Career== Šurnovská has been capped for the Slovakia national team, appearing for the team during the 2019 FIFA Women's World Cup qualifying cycle. ==References== ==External links== * * * Category:1999 births Category:Living people Category:Slovak women's footballers Category:Slovakia women's international footballers Category:Women's association football midfielders Category:Apollon Ladies F.C. players Category:Expatriate women's footballers in Cyprus Category:Slovak expatriate sportspeople in Cyprus Category:ŠK Slovan Bratislava (women) players Category:Footballers at the 2014 Summer Youth Olympics Category:SK Slavia Praha (women) players Category:Expatriate women's footballers in the Czech Republic Category:Slovak expatriate sportspeople in the Czech Republic Category:Czech First Division (women) players
title: Martina Šurnovská
